{"lemma":"أَبْلَقانِ","slug":"أَبْلَقانِ","root":"ب.ل.ق","root_slug":"ب-ل-ق","root_link":"/words/roots/ب-ل-ق","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n3254","n3256","n3263"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%92%D9%84%D9%8E%D9%82%D8%A7%D9%86%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"piebald, ablaq"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Probably from Balaq Hills, a mountain range in the Marib Governorate of Yemen, where a type of stone is used in building"},"ipa":["/ʔab.laq/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n3254","headword_ar":"ابلق","root":"blq","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a stallion)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"begot offspring such as are termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buloq","text_ar":"بُلْق"},{"kind":"text","text":"[pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abolaqu","text_ar":"اَبْلَقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.]. (Zj, K.)       -A2-  See also 1."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n3256","headword_ar":"ابلقّ","root":"blq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiboliqaAqN","text_ar":"اِبْلِقَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (IDrd, S, K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AblAq~","text_ar":"ابلاقّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IDrd, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiboliyqaAqN","text_ar":"اِبْلِيقَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (IDrd, TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ablwlq","text_ar":"ابلولق","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiboliylaAqN","text_ar":"اِبْلِيلَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baliqa","text_ar":"بَلِقَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (JK, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"balqN","text_ar":"بَلقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K, * TA; [accord. to the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"balqN","text_ar":"بَلقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", but this is a mistake;]) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baluqa","text_ar":"بَلُقَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) but IDrd asserts only the first and second of these verbs to be known; (TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a horse)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ablq","text_ar":"ابلق"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"black and white:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"white in the kind legs as high as the thighs."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)"}],"source_refs":["IDrd","K","JK","S"]},{"entry_id":"n3263","headword_ar":"اَبْلَقُ","root":"blq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", applied to a horse, fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baloqaA='u","text_ar":"بَلْقَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Black and white:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"white in the hind legs as high as the thighs:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISd, K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buloqN","text_ar":"بُلْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": which is applied by Ru-beh to mountains: but the Arabs apply the epithet"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ablq","text_ar":"ابلق"},{"kind":"text","text":"to a beast of the equine kind, and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aboraqu","text_ar":"اَبْرَقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"to a mountain (TA) and to a sheep or goat: (Lh, TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"brq","text_ar":"برق"},{"kind":"text","text":":) the former is also applied to a rope. (JK.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Talaba AlA^abolaqa","text_ar":"طَلَبَ الاَبْلَقَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEaquwqa","text_ar":"العَقُوقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(which is a prov., TA) means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He sought an impossible thing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"because"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ablq","text_ar":"ابلق"},{"kind":"text","text":"is applied to a male, and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eqwq","text_ar":"عقوق"},{"kind":"text","text":"means pregnant: or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlAblq","text_ar":"الابلق"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEqwq","text_ar":"العقوق"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the dawn;"},{"kind":"text","text":"because it breaks, (lit., cleaves,) from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaq~ahu","text_ar":"عَقَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aq~ahu","text_ar":"شَقَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","ISd","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}